x4freetext: the MC40 Cyclotron
Helium (4He) gas target was used.
Gas pressures were 420, 620, 850 and 900 mbar for
beam energies of 46 and 62 MeV.
The E- delta E particle detection system
made use of two double-sided silicon-strip detectors.
The delta-E detector was 70 mum thick and the E
detector was 1 mm thick. Both were square detectors
with a side length of 50 mm.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: . The uncertainty of TTIK measurements depend
on a lot of preliminary analysis and specific analytic
techniques, which included
-measurement of the total kinetic energy of the decay
product and position of the event on the detector,
-the energy loss of the beam, kinematics of the
reaction,
-the excitation energy of the compound nucleus and
efficiency correction
.An uncertainty on the beam energy of 10%,
which could  be resolved through data analysis.
An R-matrix analysis was performed on the data in order
to extract the spin, parities and partial widths of the
resonant states in F-18.
